<dl id="n12207d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12207d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12207d"> 207(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Let&apos;s sit where we are / not on an anthill</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Si tu entends <font color="green">[dire]</font>: &ldquo;Restons assis&rdquo;, <font color="green">[tu peux &ecirc;tre]</font> s&ucirc;r que celui dont le derri&egrave;re est &agrave; l&apos;entr&eacute;e d&apos;une fourmili&egrave;re n&apos;est pas de ceux-l&agrave; <font color="green">[qui l&apos;ont dit]</font>. <br><font color="green">[If you heard someone say &ldquo;Let&apos;s remain seated&rdquo;, you can be sure that it is not the person who is sitting with his behind at the entrance to an anthill who is speaking.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 152 (from Chapter XIX, <i>Bon sens et observation</i>, a collection of sayings)</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12204b" href="c12all.htm#c12204b">VI.C.12:204(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
